            "heading": "Angiogenic Signaling",
            "content": "BPC-157 promotes angiogenesis (new blood vessel formation) through multiple pathways. It upregulates vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) and its receptor VEGFR2, stimulating endothelial cell proliferation and migration. The peptide also interacts with the nitric oxide (NO) pathway, modulating eNOS activity to promote vasodilation and tissue perfusion. This angiogenic activity is crucial for wound healing and tissue repair.",
