                    "description": "In mice fed a high-fat diet, MOTS-c treatment prevented diet-induced obesity, improved glucose tolerance, and enhanced insulin sensitivity by 28%. These effects occurred without changes in food intake, suggesting direct metabolic effects.",
                    "quality": "Animal study (mice)",
                    "citation": {"text": "MOTS-c metabolic effects", "url": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25738459/"}
                },
                {
                    "description": "Age-dependent decline in endogenous MOTS-c levels correlates with metabolic dysfunction. Replacement in aged mice restored metabolic flexibility and improved glucose homeostasis.",
